        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 3:23PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 323 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles south of Geyser, or 20 miles southwest of Stanford, moving
northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Neihart.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
